	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jan 3rd 2:11 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is a hard cap of 30hp/tick on worn regen.<br><br>There is a &quot;soft&quot; cap of 250 on +atk, but no hard cap known.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 250 number doesn't actually affect worn +atk, but instead the atk bonus of the Avatar buff procced from Sleeper's Tomb weapons.  Gonna use a little addition to illustrate.<br><br>1-150 +atk  = everything is normal<br>151+ +atk = you get less than 100+atk from eff:Avatar on your weapons.  You only get enough to bring you up to +250 total.<br><br>Avatar (and all variations thereof) cast on you by a shaman is unaffected by this cap, and will always add the full +atk ammount.<br><br>Hope everyone could follow.  Anyhow, all this is extremely unlikely to impact more than 1% of any server.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Frelance<br>61 Archmage<br>Master of the Homos<br>Anal sex extraordinaire</td></tr>
